# Setting Up Your Celo Development Environment
## Prerequisites
- Node.js (v16 or higher)
- Yarn or npm
- A code editor (e.g., VS Code)
- Metamask or another Celo-compatible wallet
- Docker (optional for running a local node)

## Steps
1. Install Celo CLI: `npm install -g @celo/celocli`
2. Set up a wallet and fund it with testnet Celo Gold via the [Alfajores faucet](https://faucet.celo.org).
3. Configure your project to connect to the Alfajores testnet (see `docs/alfajores-testnet.md`).
4. Install Celo Composer: `npx @celo/celo-composer@latest create`
